name: cellular response to organic cyclic compound
description: "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organic cyclic compound stimulus." [GOC:mah]

name: catalytic activity, acting on a protein
description: "Catalytic activity that acts to modify a protein." [GOC:molecular_function_refactoring, GOC:pdt]

name: response to organic cyclic compound
description: "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organic cyclic compound stimulus." [GOC:ef]

name: brassinosteroid mediated signaling pathway
description: "The series of molecular signals mediated by the detection of brassinosteroid." [GOC:sm]

name: steroid hormone receptor signaling pathway
description: "The series of molecular signals mediated by a steroid hormone binding to a receptor." [PMID:12606724]

name: response to steroid hormone
description: "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a steroid hormone stimulus." [GOC:go_curators]

name: cellular response to brassinosteroid stimulus
description: "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a brassinosteroid stimulus." [GOC:mah]

name: cellular response to steroid hormone stimulus
description: "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a steroid hormone stimulus." [GOC:mah]

name: response to brassinosteroid
description: "Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a brassinosteroid stimulus." [GOC:jl]

name: phosphotransferase activity, alcohol group as acceptor
description: "Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to an alcohol group (acceptor)." [EC:2.7.1.-]

name: transferase activity
description: "Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2." [EC:2.-.-.-]
